The paper deals with search systems in online social media sites, which suggests that it falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category. The focus on bias in search results and the use of algorithms to rank results suggests that it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. The paper specifically deals with politics-related queries on Twitter, which suggests that it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC) category. The use of natural language processing techniques to analyze bias in search results suggests that it could also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) category. Finally, the discussion of possible mechanisms to signal bias in social media search systems' interfaces suggests that it could also belong to the Computers and Society (cs.CY) category.
